Description: St Anthony (or St Jerome?), sitting at a table with crucifix in right hand, and repelling the devil in the guise of a naked woman; night scene lit by candlelight Engraving
Curator's comments: See: Stéphane Loire, Prints after Guercino, 'Print Quarterly', v.VIII, no. 2, June 1991, pp. 159-150, fig. 68.
